4.0 ACCIDENT HISTORY
There have been no accidental releases of anhydrous ammonia at the JOWCT facility in the last five years that have resulted in death, injury, or significant property damage on site or off-site death, injury, evacuation, sheltering in place, property damage, or environmental damage.

5.0 EMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM
The JOWCT facility has implemented a detailed written Emergency Response Plan (ERP).  The ERP is intended to address all emergencies at the facility, in addition to incidents related to a release of anhydrous ammonia.  The ERP includes:
* Coordination with the local fire department and with the Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC);
* Emergency escape procedures and emergency escape route assignments;
* Procedures to be followed by employees who remain to operate critical plant operations before they evacuate;
* Procedures to account for all employees after emergency evacuation has been completed;
* What personal protective equipment and spill response equipment is available;
* The preferred means of reporting fires and other emergencies;
* Names of persons or departments who can be contacted for further information or explanation of duties under the plan; and
* Designation and training of a sufficient number of persons to assist in the safe and orderly evacuation of employees.
